00:05:31.600 --> 00:05:37.760
Technical Analysis of Stock Trends. It came out in 1938 and it is still in print. It's now in its

00:05:37.760 --> 00:05:42.959
11th edition, I think. This book by William Gilers from the late 1960s was put out by Standard and

00:05:42.959 --> 00:05:48.480
Poor's. The idea was that if you looked at trends in stock prices, either for the market as a whole

00:05:48.480 --> 00:05:53.359
or for individual stocks, you could spot recurring patterns and patterns that told you what might

00:05:53.359 --> 00:05:59.119
happen next. Not infallibly, of course, but enough to give you an edge, to let you make an informed

00:05:59.119 --> 00:06:04.399
