00:09:13.599 --> 00:09:18.000
market, asset prices reflect all available information, or at least all publicly available

00:09:18.000 --> 00:09:24.159
information about an asset. So in the short run, prices follow a random walk. That means you can't

00:09:24.159 --> 00:09:30.000
consistently beat the market, at least not like this. The technical analysis people were just

00:09:30.000 --> 00:09:35.679
reading patterns into noise. Sure, sometimes it worked, but in the long run, you wouldn't

00:09:35.679 --> 00:09:41.119
outperform an index fund, except by luck. I wanted to write a little tiny bit of code to generate

